Text.Value: Are you all right...?
And they both answered.
Leave.
It was the start of something incredible - two heroes on the hunt for justice, no matter the cost.
Perhaps this was where the journey was meant to start after all...
*Meow!*
*Rrrriow!*
This could be the beginning of something. Two heroes against the world, enacting justice for those unable to seek their own.
All the tall one had to do was say yes.
*HISS!*

Text.Value: Chase the cat away.
Hello, sour puss. Do you want scritches?
Leave.
*...Purr.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Animation of PLYR petting the cat. [Gwen Lee]

Text.Value: Strangers? Only in a fool's definition of the word.
Destiny is a fickle mistress. She showers you in riches one day and kicks you into the gutter the next. But today, she smiles.
Upon their return, the cat couldn't help but wonder whether the tall one had finally decided how their die would be cast.
Perhaps it was simply not meant to be...
I don't think I'm the partner for you - but Derryth Bonecloak be just who you're looking for.
*Meow...?*
It was in the tall one's voice: they knew they cared about this creature but they didn't know why. But the cat did.
*...Mrrrr. Meow.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Please reuse CAT_Rig_CINE_Aggresive_Idle_01 for the hiss. <Gwen Lee>

Text.Value: The tall one had failed the first test: they lacked caution. The cat could have just as easily been a foe as a potential friend.
Do you want to come with me?
*The cat seems to be trying very hard to remain aloof - and not wholly succeeding.*
Attempt to pet the cat.
The cat beheld the one who'd delivered him from the streets while taking on the heavy burden of justice alone. He purred.

EditorData.NodeContext: Intense narration - but a little softer/more content now

Text.Value: When would they be ready? Only the tall one - and fate - truly knew.
Leave.
Sorry - our destines aren't meant to intertwine.
Two heroes were fated to cross paths that day. Their eyes met. Destiny was calling...
It was another day in the city of lies. Baldur's Gate - where the people begged for justice until they starved.
The tall one had passed the first test. The second would come when they were ready - and not before.
Yes! Join me!
If you're brave enough, I'm sure Derryth Bonecloak at the apothecary will pet you all you want.
The tall one volunteered another - the apothecary. A principled dwarf - a scritcher of heads, and a giver of scraps.
*...Meow.*
*Hiss!*

Excuse me?

Synopsis: A cat you can send over to Derryth Bonecloak if Baelen is dead. It speaks in rolled r's and is very difficult to understand.
